messages.text:
Telegram recently introduced a feature to import WhatsApp chats. You do this by opening an exported ZIP-archive of the chat with Telegram in the share menu on your phone.

I don't think it's designed to work with exported chats from Telegram itself, but there might be a way to make it work.

messages.text:
It can be done but you have to do it yourself. I did it by looking at how the whatsapp backup file was generated (text only), Then I made a program that converts an old Telegram backup from html to whatsapp txt, Finally I used an mtproto library (telethon) to import the file by calling the import method directly and uploading the generated file.
HomeAloneDaddyTony
â€¢
2 yr. ago

Would you be able to share the program you were using? It must be very helpful for other people using Telegram!

text:
It wouldn't help much because the HTML parser was made for a format no longer used by Telegram, they changed a lot of the HTML, plus it only works if the backup was text only.

Also, the script was done very quickly and therefore didn't work with the first and/or last file, and there is a lot of hard-coded information.
Also I think I have manually modified part of the first and/or last file to make it work, to do it quickly.

In short, it will never work and would have to be completely rewritten.

This is the code, good luck
